from kwyatt kershner wyatt subject re quality of catholic liturgy in article crep stephen a crep write in article jemurray john e murray write on palm sunday at my parish we be invite to take the role of jesu in the passion i decline to participate last year at the liturgy meet i point out how we crucify christ by my sin so therefore it be appropriate that we retain the role of the crowd but to no avail musician reader and so on new thing be introduce in the course of the liturgy and since no one know what happen the new thing have to be explain and pretty soon instead of do a lot of the mas we just sit there listen or space out in my case to how the mas be about to be do in my mind i lay the blame on liturgy committee make up of lay person to be aware of the lord presence a a former catholic and now a a very active lutheran it be some of the innovation of the mas which make me leave the catholic church and return to the more traditional catholic chuch the lutheran i spend many year a a lector read the passion part a appropriate in the catholic church and i find it very meaningful my lutheran parish just institute the tenebra service for good friday and i wa the lector for a paraphrase passion which wa exceptional i hear and learn thing that i have previously overlook in the gospel yet those fact be alway there a a matter of interest the pastor and i be talk about the difference between the rc and lutheran church during holy week over breakfast easter sunday a a member of a liturgy committee i can tell you that the problem be certain person dominate who want to try out all kind of innovation the priest do seem even to want to make any decision of their own in many case i gues it easier to try something new than it be to refuse to allow it my wife be the member of the liturgy committee in the family call music and worship at my church my pastor do have control of thi committee but listen very carefully to the committee suggestion it need a strong hand to lead and guide to keep the intent and the message clear and strong a it should be through lent and the rest of the liturgical year additional reason for my leave the catholic faith lack of any selfles spiritual guidance by priest in my parish aka wishy-washy a you may gather from my comment i feel that it be very important ir regardles of denominational guideline to have a which promote the true reason that we be gather there i be quite comfortable in a traditional mas with receive holy communion on the tongue the sacrament of penance not reconciliation station of the cros so on and so forth the reason other type of mass and parish exist be because these feel be not share by everyone i want more person to attend church and to find the lord but i do want them attend a show it not my church work hard to have a meaningful service during lent on wednesday but follow traditional lutheran book of worship guideline where thing be change or omit during lent such a the hymn of praise it be note so that we be aware of the reason that it be not there quite frankly it be very hard for a non-catholic to go to a mas and fit in my dear wife never could former methodist and holy week mass and vigil would intimidate the daylight out of a non-catholic those catholic who have bear with me thi far understand what i mean please keep in mind why we be there to gather together in worship not to worry about how something be do or not do if there be something wrong that you feel need address by all mean talk to ymy priest or pastor i have only ever meet one who would listen they be there to provide spiritual guidance and to help use them my difference with the catholic church be much more fundamental but my decision to change faith wa do with prayer intervention and session with priest and minister in christ kershner kershner wyatt kwyatt my opinion be my own and be necessarily my employer 